#   CODE-007: graf/LOG.c: reuse BLOB/GIT descent & parsers

graf/LOG.c is the dir's redundancy hotspot: it re-hand-rolls (commit,path)→blob tree-descent that BLOB.c already gives via GRAFTreeStep/GRAFPathDescend/GRAFBlobAtCommit, re-rolls the `Name <email> ts tz` author parsing GIT.h provides, and the first-parent walk plus the commit-fetch-and-type preamble are pasted across DAG/LOG/GRAF.exe. Route LOG.c through the existing helpers.

##  Issues

LOG.c duplicates tree-descent, author parsing, and the first-parent fetch loop.

 -  LOG.c:360-403 re-rolls (commit,path)→blob descent; BLOB.c:15-49 has GRAFBlobAtCommit (used by BLAME/REBASE).
 -  graflog_parse_author (LOG.c:171,228) hand-rolls the ident parsing GIT.h::GITu8s* already does.
 -  first-parent fetch + GITu8sDrainCommit + hex→sha pasted at DAG.c:295, LOG.c:329, GRAF.exe.c:88.
 -  KEEPGet + type!=COMMIT bail preamble recurs ~15x (BLOB.c:54, GET.c:640, LOG.c:365).

##  Blockers

None; graf-internal, mostly LOG.c.

##  Planned

Replace LOG.c's hand-rolled walks with the BLOB/GIT helpers; factor the fetch preamble.

 -  Repro first (§17): graf log output over a fixture stays byte-identical.
 -  LOG descent → GRAFBlobAtCommit; author → the GITu8s ident parser.
 -  One first-parent helper; one GRAFCommitAt(h)→body+type preamble.

